<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1059,499,697]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078">
D i a g n o s i s: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2019" box="[346,550,499,520]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alborzensis">
<emphasis box="[346,550,499,520]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078">Colletes alborzensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fourcroy" baseAuthorityYear="1785" box="[706,868,499,520]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fodiens">
<emphasis box="[706,868,499,520]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078">Colletes fodiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group and is most closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Noskiewicz" authorityYear="1936" box="[415,571,529,550]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inexpectatus">
<emphasis box="[415,571,529,550]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078">C. inexpectatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
NOSKIEWICZ. The female of the new species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Noskiewicz" authorityYear="1936" box="[308,465,558,580]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inexpectatus">
<emphasis box="[308,465,558,580]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078">C. inexpectatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and only differs by a combination of the following subtle characters: Eyes slightly more converging below and clypeus more convex with apical grooves a bit larger (
<figureCitation box="[361,453,617,639]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="2.[151,191,1519,1541]" captionTargetBox="[152,1055,416,1501]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1055,416,1502]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-6: Colletes alborzensis nov.sp., female: (1) head; (2) metasomal terga T1-T2; C. alborzensis nov.sp., male: (3) hind basitarsus; C. inexpectatus NOSKIEWICZ, female: (4) head; (5) metasomal terga T1-T2; C. inexpectatus, male (6) hind basitarsus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741949/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078">Figs 1, 4</figureCitation>
), punctation on the disc of T1 slightly finer (
<figureCitation box="[908,999,616,639]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="2.[151,191,1519,1541]" captionTargetBox="[152,1055,416,1501]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1055,416,1502]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-6: Colletes alborzensis nov.sp., female: (1) head; (2) metasomal terga T1-T2; C. alborzensis nov.sp., male: (3) hind basitarsus; C. inexpectatus NOSKIEWICZ, female: (4) head; (5) metasomal terga T1-T2; C. inexpectatus, male (6) hind basitarsus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741949/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078">Figs 2, 5</figureCitation>
). The male is identifiable by the characteristic shape of S7 (
<figureCitation box="[716,824,646,668]" captionStart="Figs 7-11" captionStartId="3.[618,658,954,976]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[157,1060,198,1280]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 7-11: Colletes alborzensis nov.sp., male: (7) metasomal terga T1-T2; (8) metasomal sternum S7; (9) gonostylus; Colletes inexpectatus NOSKIEWICZ, male: (10) metasomal terga T1- T2; (11) metasomal sternum S7." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741951/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078">Figs 8, 11</figureCitation>
), denser punctation of metasomal terga (
<figureCitation box="[331,434,675,697]" captionStart="Figs 7-11" captionStartId="3.[618,658,954,976]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[157,1060,198,1280]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 7-11: Colletes alborzensis nov.sp., male: (7) metasomal terga T1-T2; (8) metasomal sternum S7; (9) gonostylus; Colletes inexpectatus NOSKIEWICZ, male: (10) metasomal terga T1- T2; (11) metasomal sternum S7." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741951/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078">Figs 7, 10</figureCitation>
) and slightly longer but narrower hind basitarsi (
<figureCitation box="[930,1022,675,697]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="2.[151,191,1519,1541]" captionTargetBox="[152,1055,416,1501]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1055,416,1502]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-6: Colletes alborzensis nov.sp., female: (1) head; (2) metasomal terga T1-T2; C. alborzensis nov.sp., male: (3) hind basitarsus; C. inexpectatus NOSKIEWICZ, female: (4) head; (5) metasomal terga T1-T2; C. inexpectatus, male (6) hind basitarsus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741949/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078">Figs 3, 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="1079" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,350,713,735]" box="[151,350,713,735]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078">D e s c r i p t i o n</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1059,750,1271]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078">
F e m a l e: Body length: 8.0– 
<quantity box="[501,588,750,772]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078" unit="mm" value="8.5">8.5 mm</quantity>
. Head distinctly wider than long (
<figureCitation box="[976,1043,750,772]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="2.[151,191,1519,1541]" captionTargetBox="[152,1055,416,1501]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1055,416,1502]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-6: Colletes alborzensis nov.sp., female: (1) head; (2) metasomal terga T1-T2; C. alborzensis nov.sp., male: (3) hind basitarsus; C. inexpectatus NOSKIEWICZ, female: (4) head; (5) metasomal terga T1-T2; C. inexpectatus, male (6) hind basitarsus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741949/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Integument black, mandible apically dark reddish-brown. Face sparsely covered with moderately long greyish, erect hair, on vertex hair shorter (
<figureCitation box="[791,855,809,831]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="2.[151,191,1519,1541]" captionTargetBox="[152,1055,416,1501]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1055,416,1502]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-6: Colletes alborzensis nov.sp., female: (1) head; (2) metasomal terga T1-T2; C. alborzensis nov.sp., male: (3) hind basitarsus; C. inexpectatus NOSKIEWICZ, female: (4) head; (5) metasomal terga T1-T2; C. inexpectatus, male (6) hind basitarsus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741949/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Clypeus strongly convex, with a shallow longitudinal median depression, supraclypeal area almost rectangular, large and slightly convex in profile. Clypeus finely, regularly and densely punctate (i &lt;0.5d); surface between punctures smooth and shiny, inconspicuous pair of apical clypeal depressions (
<figureCitation box="[427,485,926,948]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="2.[151,191,1519,1541]" captionTargetBox="[152,1055,416,1501]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1055,416,1502]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-6: Colletes alborzensis nov.sp., female: (1) head; (2) metasomal terga T1-T2; C. alborzensis nov.sp., male: (3) hind basitarsus; C. inexpectatus NOSKIEWICZ, female: (4) head; (5) metasomal terga T1-T2; C. inexpectatus, male (6) hind basitarsus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741949/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Malar area medially narrow, about 1/2 as long as width of mandible base, finely punctate and partly shiny. Antenna black. Scutum on disc impunctate and shiny, laterally finely and densely punctate (i &lt;0.5d), between punctures smooth and shiny. Scutellum anteriomedially impunctate, smooth and shiny; rest of scutellum densely and coarsely punctate (i &lt;0.5d). Thorax sparsely covered with long greyish hair. Wings fuscous, venation blackish-brown. Legs black, vestiture whitish, scopa white. Integument of metasoma black, apical tergal depressions narrowly translucent dark yellowish-brown (
<figureCitation box="[343,411,1131,1153]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="2.[151,191,1519,1541]" captionTargetBox="[152,1055,416,1501]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1055,416,1502]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-6: Colletes alborzensis nov.sp., female: (1) head; (2) metasomal terga T1-T2; C. alborzensis nov.sp., male: (3) hind basitarsus; C. inexpectatus NOSKIEWICZ, female: (4) head; (5) metasomal terga T1-T2; C. inexpectatus, male (6) hind basitarsus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741949/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Terga on disc with few short, erect, greyish hairs, apical depressions apical hair bands (
<figureCitation box="[458,519,1161,1183]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="2.[151,191,1519,1541]" captionTargetBox="[152,1055,416,1501]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1055,416,1502]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-6: Colletes alborzensis nov.sp., female: (1) head; (2) metasomal terga T1-T2; C. alborzensis nov.sp., male: (3) hind basitarsus; C. inexpectatus NOSKIEWICZ, female: (4) head; (5) metasomal terga T1-T2; C. inexpectatus, male (6) hind basitarsus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741949/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). T1 apically only very slightly depressed, depression superficially and finely punctuate, apical margin impunctate (
<figureCitation box="[835,906,1190,1212]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="2.[151,191,1519,1541]" captionTargetBox="[152,1055,416,1501]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1055,416,1502]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-6: Colletes alborzensis nov.sp., female: (1) head; (2) metasomal terga T1-T2; C. alborzensis nov.sp., male: (3) hind basitarsus; C. inexpectatus NOSKIEWICZ, female: (4) head; (5) metasomal terga T1-T2; C. inexpectatus, male (6) hind basitarsus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741949/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). T1 on disc moderately dense (i = 0.5–1.0d) and relatively finely punctate, between punctures smooth and shiny (
<figureCitation box="[263,325,1249,1271]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="2.[151,191,1519,1541]" captionTargetBox="[152,1055,416,1501]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1055,416,1502]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-6: Colletes alborzensis nov.sp., female: (1) head; (2) metasomal terga T1-T2; C. alborzensis nov.sp., male: (3) hind basitarsus; C. inexpectatus NOSKIEWICZ, female: (4) head; (5) metasomal terga T1-T2; C. inexpectatus, male (6) hind basitarsus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741949/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). No apical sternal hair bands but instead some long, erect ciliae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1059,1286,1601]" lastBlockId="2.[151,971,211,233]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="1079" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078">
M a l e: Body length: 8.0– 
<quantity box="[446,527,1286,1308]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078" unit="mm" value="8.5">8.5 mm</quantity>
. Head distinctly wider than long. Integument black except tips of mandible partly dark reddish-brown. Face densely covered with long, yellowish-white, erect hairs. Malar area medially about half as long as width of mandible base, finely striate. Antenna black. Mesosoma. Integument black. Mesoscutal disc coarsely and sparsely punctate (i = 1–2d), smooth and shiny. Mesoscutum, scutellum, metanotum, mesepisternum and propodeum covered with long yellowish-white, erect hairs. Wings transparent; wing venation blackish-brown. Legs. Integument black. Hind basitarsus apically broadened (
<figureCitation box="[362,425,1491,1513]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="2.[151,191,1519,1541]" captionTargetBox="[152,1055,416,1501]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1055,416,1502]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-6: Colletes alborzensis nov.sp., female: (1) head; (2) metasomal terga T1-T2; C. alborzensis nov.sp., male: (3) hind basitarsus; C. inexpectatus NOSKIEWICZ, female: (4) head; (5) metasomal terga T1-T2; C. inexpectatus, male (6) hind basitarsus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741949/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Vestiture whitish to greyish-brown. Metasoma. Integument black except narrow apical margins of terga reddish translucent. Discs of T1 – T2 covered with long, erect whitish hairs that are apically successively shorter (
<figureCitation box="[849,912,1550,1572]" captionStart="Figs 7-11" captionStartId="3.[618,658,954,976]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[157,1060,198,1280]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 7-11: Colletes alborzensis nov.sp., male: (7) metasomal terga T1-T2; (8) metasomal sternum S7; (9) gonostylus; Colletes inexpectatus NOSKIEWICZ, male: (10) metasomal terga T1- T2; (11) metasomal sternum S7." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741951/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1078">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); apical tergal hair bands broad, white. Terga densely and finely punctate (i &lt;d), between punctures smooth and shiny (
<figureCitation box="[344,406,211,233]" captionStart="Figs 7-11" captionStartId="3.[618,658,954,976]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[157,1060,198,1280]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 7-11: Colletes alborzensis nov.sp., male: (7) metasomal terga T1-T2; (8) metasomal sternum S7; (9) gonostylus; Colletes inexpectatus NOSKIEWICZ, male: (10) metasomal terga T1- T2; (11) metasomal sternum S7." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741951/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1079">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Terminalia. Genitalia and S7 as illustrated (
<figureCitation box="[866,958,211,233]" captionStart="Figs 7-11" captionStartId="3.[618,658,954,976]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[157,1060,198,1280]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 7-11: Colletes alborzensis nov.sp., male: (7) metasomal terga T1-T2; (8) metasomal sternum S7; (9) gonostylus; Colletes inexpectatus NOSKIEWICZ, male: (10) metasomal terga T1- T2; (11) metasomal sternum S7." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741951/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1079">Figs 8–9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="1079" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1058,249,300]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1079">
E t y m o l o g y: The species is named after the 
<collectingRegion box="[694,882,249,271]" country="Iran" name="Alborz" pageId="2" pageNumber="1079">Alborz Mountains</collectingRegion>
in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1017,1058,249,270]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="1079">Iran</collectingCountry>
where specimens of the new species were collected.
</paragraph>
